patrick lawler stanford department of classics skip to navigation department of classics standford university logo header home people programs courses projects news events resources contact patrick lawler contact information http www omm com patricklawler biography patrick lawler graduated in 1989 majoring in classical studies honors and distinction phi beta kappa and spent a semester abroad in rome at the american center for classical studies mark edwards was his thesis advisor for an undergraduate thesis on book 23 of the iliad the funeral games of patroklos patrick also worked on the harvard university of chicago archaeological dig in ashkelon israel in 1987 where he personally worked in a pet cemetery one of the very few outside egypt and beverly hills after college he cashed in his cards and went to law school at university of chicago patrick is now a counsel in o melveny's century city office and is a member of the corporate finance capital markets practice where he concentrates principally in the areas of debt financing transactions secured unsecured asset based and cash flow based with an emphasis on entertainment financings acquisitions and highly leveraged financings email stanford classics find us on facebook address & phone search upcoming events christopher krebs stepping out from his own shadow caesar as a man of letters 02 09 2012 felipe rojas gergas nannas semiramis picturing the past in roman asia minor 02 13 2012 alicia jimenez original copy imitation and colonialism in roman hispania 02 16 2012 see more site info 2012 stanford university department of classics all rights reserved site design by chapter three login login with sunet speaker request webform for faculty stanford classics wikisite powered by drupal an open source content management system
